A pilot had a lucky escape on Friday after a light aircraft crashed near Lanseria  International Airport in Gauteng. Emer-G-Med paramedics responded just after 10am  and found the wreckage of the small aircraft in a field. “The pilot and only occupant was found on the scene and treated for moderate injuries,” said the service. Emer-G-Med  said investigations will be conducted by aviation authorities. TimesLIVE